article.headline: UAB 87, Tulane 82
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Marvett McDonald and Paul Delaney scored 13 points each to help lift UAB to an 87-82 victory over Tulane on Wednesday night. UAB (18-5, 8-2 Conference USA) had five players in double digit scoring with Lawrence Kinnard, Derrick Broom and Wen Mukubu all scoring 12 points. Carldell "Squeaky" Johnson hit the biggest shot of the night with UAB leading 82-80 when he sank a 3-pointer as the buzzer sounded with 16.5 seconds left in the game. Johnson finished with nine points and tied his career-high 11 assists. Quincy Davis had 20 points and 10 rebounds to lead Tulane (9-14, 4-6). Ryan Williams scored 17 points for the Green Wave and Chris Moore had 15 points on 5-for-5 shooting from 3-point range. David Gomez added 12 points and six rebounds. Tulane jumped to an early 7-5 lead, but UAB went on a 14-0 run to pull ahead 19-7. The Blazers led 42-36 at the half and their biggest lead came at 76-63 with 7:25 left to play, but Tulane did not give up. Moore hit two 3s, Andrew Garcia added another and Davis hit six free throws to pull the Green Wave within two points, but Johnson's buzzer-beating score sealed the victory for UAB.
